Milpitas.KDTV-DT: KDTV-DT, virtual channel 14 (UHF digital channel 51), is a Univision owned-and-operated television station licensed to San Francisco, California, United States and serving the San Francisco Bay Area. The station is owned by the Univision Local Media subsidiary of Univision Communications, as part of a duopoly with Vallejo-licensed UniMás owned-and-operated station KFSF-DT (channel 66). The two stations share studios located at 1940 Zanker Road in San Jose; KDTV's transmitter is located on Mission Peak in Fremont.
